Bluetooth is a wireless technology standard for exchanging data over short 
distances (using short-wavelength UHF radio waves in the ISM band from 2.4 to 
2.485 GHz[4]) from fixed and mobile devices, and building personal 
area networks (PANs). 

1. hciconfig  is used to configure Bluetooth devices.
 hciconfig -a hciX up
2. hcitool  is  used to configure Bluetooth connections and send some special 
command to Bluetooth devices. 
 hcitool -i <hciX> dev
3.hcidump  reads raw HCI data coming from and going to a Bluetooth device and
prints to screen commands, events and data in a human-readable form.
hcidump -h

ussp-push - Client for OBEX PUSH
ussp-push-dbg - Client for OBEX PUSH (debugging information)
wiipdf - present a PDF file using your wiimote
this one works with the wii mote^
